  • Constructor Details

    • ScoreRecord

      public ScoreRecord​(java.lang.String m_SetName, java.lang.String m_LevelName, java.lang.String m_FastestTime, java.lang.String m_PlayerOfFT, java.lang.String m_MinimumMove, java.lang.String m_PlayerOfMM)
      ScoreRecord constructor to initialize all information stored in this object by given parameters.
      It is DataManager's job to instantiate new ScoreRecord, update and save them into file.
      Parameters:
      m_SetName - String value specifying set name.
      m_LevelName - String value specifying level name.
      m_FastestTime - String value specifying formatted fastest time.
      m_PlayerOfFT - String value specifying record breaker's name of the fastest time.
      m_MinimumMove - String value specifying minimum move.
      m_PlayerOfMM - String value specifying record breaker's name of the minimum move.
      See Also:
      DataManager.getTopRecord()
